### P0-4: Weekly Attendance Dashboard Makes 7 Separate API Calls

**Location:** [attendanceService.ts](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/suffacampus-webpanel/services/attendanceService.ts#L143-L163)

```typescript
static async getWeeklyAttendance(schoolId) {
  return await Promise.all(
    days.map(async (day, index) => {
      // 7 calls to getAttendanceStats → each calls getAttendance → GET /attendance
      const stats = await AttendanceService.getAttendanceStats(schoolId, date);
    })
  );
}
```

**Root Cause:** `getWeeklyAttendance` fires **7 parallel requests** (one per day), each fetching ALL attendance records for that date, then computing stats client-side.

**Impact:** On dashboard load: 7 × (full attendance fetch for entire school) = massive data transfer. For a school with 500 students × 7 days = up to 3,500 records fetched and discarded. **Backend has `/attendance/stats` endpoint that does this server-side** — webpanel ignores it entirely.

