## 4. P1 Issues (HIGH — Fix Before Scaling)

### P1-1: `requirePasswordChange` Not Enforced on Webpanel

**Location:** [login/page.tsx](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/suffacampus-webpanel/app/login/page.tsx)

The backend returns `requirePasswordChange: true` for auto-provisioned student/teacher accounts. The mobile app handles this (redirects to password change screen). The **webpanel does not check this flag** — user logs in and proceeds normally with a weak password (`FirstName@123`).

> [!WARNING]  
> This means newly created student/teacher accounts can be accessed by anyone who knows the naming pattern.

---

### P1-2: Webpanel Middleware Auth Check is Cookie-Based — Easily Bypassable

**Location:** [middleware.ts](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/suffacampus-webpanel/middleware.ts#L129-L132)

```typescript
const authCookie =
  request.cookies.get('__session') ??
  request.cookies.get('SuffaCampus-token');
const isAuthenticated = Boolean(authCookie?.value);
```

The webpanel's Next.js middleware checks for cookie **existence only** — not validity. Any non-empty cookie value passes. This is mitigated by backend API auth on every data call, but it means the **route guard is theater** — a user can manually set a cookie and see the dashboard skeleton (without data).

---

### P1-3: Webpanel `getAttendanceById` Fetches Entire Day's Records

**Location:** [attendanceService.ts](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/suffacampus-webpanel/services/attendanceService.ts#L62-L65)

```typescript
static async getAttendanceById(schoolId, id) {
  const records = await AttendanceService.getAttendance(schoolId); // ALL records for today
  return records.find((a) => a.id === id) ?? null;
}
```

Fetching ALL attendance records to find ONE by ID is O(n) on the client.

---

### P1-4: Mobile `getAttendanceByStudent` Fetches Today Only

**Location:** [attendanceService.ts](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/suffacampus-mobile/services/attendanceService.ts#L70-L80)

```typescript
export async function getAttendanceByStudent(studentId) {
  const today = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0];
  const records = await apiFetch("/attendance", { params: { date: today } });
  return records.filter((r) => r.studentId === studentId);
}
```

This function fetches ALL school attendance for today, then filters client-side. Inefficient and potentially leaks other students' attendance data.

---

### P1-5: Student Email Uses Internal Domain — Not Real Email

**Location:** [student.service.ts](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/backend/src/services/student.service.ts#L141)

```typescript
const email = `${username}.${schoolId}@SuffaCampus.internal`;
```

This is fine as a login identifier, but means:
- Students cannot receive password reset emails
- No email-based notifications possible
- The `.internal` TLD won't resolve — Firebase may reject it in future updates

---

### P1-6: `Accountant` and `Principal` Roles Missing from Backend RBAC

**Location:** [permission.service.ts](file:///d:/suffacampus/apps/backend/src/services/permission.service.ts#L3)

```typescript
export const ROLES = ["SuperAdmin", "Admin", "Staff", "Teacher", "Parent", "Student"] as const;
```

The webpanel middleware defines `Accountant` and `Principal` roles with specific ACLs, but the **backend permission service doesn't recognize them**. Any user with `role: "Accountant"` or `role: "Principal"` will be treated as having **no permissions** — every API call will return 403.

> [!CAUTION]  
> If a school creates an Accountant user, they will be completely locked out of all data.

